The problem involves finding if a friend request between two people is possible. We can solve this problem using a graph traversal approach. We create a boolean array `visited` to keep track of visited nodes and a boolean array `result` to store the result of each request. We iterate through the requests and for each request, we check if the source person (`u`) and the destination person (`v`) are allowed to be friends according to the restrictions. If they are allowed, we mark the destination person (`v`) as visited. The time complexity is O(n) because we only iterate through the requests once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a boolean array to store the result and another boolean array to mark visited nodes. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only requires a small amount of energy to process each request.

